23:05.118 --> 23:06.641
So imagine what I look like now.

23:06.661 --> 23:08.264
And I still need to lose weight.

23:08.344 --> 23:08.765
I get that.

23:08.825 --> 23:09.406
I'm working on it.

23:09.446 --> 23:10.108
It's a process.

23:10.829 --> 23:13.234
But imagine what I look like now plus like 40 pounds.

23:13.666 --> 23:15.188
So it was not a good situation.

23:15.549 --> 23:29.630
I was in grad school full-time, I was working full-time, I was traveling back and forth for work, like two and a half months out of the year in a rental car, we had just had a newborn, we're up late, I'm grabbing, eating anything and everything, whatever's convenient, not thinking, not being disciplined, nothing.

23:29.650 --> 23:33.857
And I'm laying in bed one night and my heart is just pounding inside my chest.

23:33.877 --> 23:36.020
Like I'm laying still, I shouldn't be stressed out about anything.

23:36.601 --> 23:37.783
Can't get my heart to stop beating.

23:38.624 --> 23:42.610
