24:23.921 --> 24:25.263
I want to serve them as long as possible.

24:25.283 --> 24:31.050
And for whatever reason, God has blessed me to be put in a position where it's my job to serve and love this particular community.

24:31.351 --> 24:33.453
And I want to do it for as long as he will have me.

24:33.894 --> 24:37.458
So in order to do that, and I am now motivated to take better care of myself.

24:37.922 --> 24:39.344
That is my motivation.

24:39.564 --> 24:42.708
What is yours for your goal, for what you're chasing?

24:43.669 --> 24:45.511
And is what you're chasing a dream or is it a goal?

24:45.611 --> 24:51.498
Paul Levesque, who you might know is Triple H from the WWE, has this to say about the difference between a dream or a goal.

24:52.460 --> 24:56.545
A dream is something you fantasize about that isn't going to happen.

24:57.185 --> 24:59.909
A goal is something you set a plan, work for, and you achieve.

25:00.509 --> 25:04.274
And part of this process is that you have to set a goal that motivates you.

25:05.154 --> 25:06.415
Set goals that motivate you.

25:06.435 --> 25:10.239
So whenever you start this process, get something that fires you up that's personal.

25:10.279 --> 25:15.064
It is going to keep you going day after day after day when the time gets hard, when things pop up.

25:16.145 --> 25:18.607
Now, after you do this, motivation alone is not going to work.

25:18.627 --> 25:20.709
