25:46.787 --> 25:48.148
So this is a bad dude.

25:48.168 --> 25:49.390
And Lafe Baven is exactly the same.

25:49.410 --> 25:50.652
I don't know quite as much about him.

25:51.072 --> 25:56.519
But in this book, it details a process that the Navy SEALs use whenever they're selecting missions, whether they're moving forward.

25:56.860 --> 26:01.906
So I'm not going to go through the whole thing, but I do have some points I think would be helpful for you when it comes to planning your mission.

26:02.178 --> 26:04.421
And the first step is simply to analyze your mission.

26:04.561 --> 26:06.022
Analyze what that might be.

26:06.042 --> 26:07.324
And this is a feeling in your notes.

26:08.105 --> 26:09.827
You've got to find a mission that is personal.

26:09.847 --> 26:14.072
You need to identify it, analyze it, write it down, know what your mission is.

26:14.853 --> 26:16.134
So I analyze your mission.

26:16.675 --> 26:18.677
Step two, identify your assets.

26:20.219 --> 26:21.060
And what might those be?

26:21.080 --> 26:21.841
It might be money.

26:21.941 --> 26:22.762
It might be time.

26:22.802 --> 26:24.264
It might be the resources around you.

26:24.524 --> 26:28.008
It might be the people that can help you get from where you are to where you want to be.

26:28.168 --> 26:29.810
Identify those assets.

26:29.954 --> 26:32.879
Then once you do that, step three, determine your plan.

26:33.480 --> 26:40.813
And as you determine your plan, I would encourage you to make it specific and encourage you to make it simple so that you don't forget it so that it's not too muddy.

26:40.833 --> 26:44.819
And so as you get into the weeds, you can remember exactly what it is and remember why you're doing it.

26:45.040 --> 26:46.342
Going back to that motivation piece.

26:47.043 --> 26:49.568
Step four, plan for contingencies.

26:49.588 --> 26:50.890
Plan for bad things to happen.

26:50.910 --> 26:52.052
Plan for bumps in the road.

26:52.452 --> 26:55.698
There are going to be things that are going to pop up that are going to knock you off your path.

26:55.938 --> 26:58.381
So with me, for the weight loss, whatever it is, what if we go out to eat?

26:58.681 --> 27:00.763
What if there's like a giant ham in front of me at Christmas?

27:01.464 --> 27:02.646
What if I have to travel a lot?

27:02.666 --> 27:03.807
What if we do this, that or the other?

27:03.907 --> 27:04.708
Plan for those things.

27:04.748 --> 27:05.789
Don't let them surprise you.

27:06.330 --> 27:08.432
Step five, mitigate your risks.

27:08.933 --> 27:11.295
Mitigate meaning to lessen the severity of.

27:12.276 --> 27:14.999
So an example I can use when I talk about this is maybe it's your Bible reading.

27:15.360 --> 27:20.426
You wanna go from reading the Bible 0.0 times a week and you wanna start reading a little bit more.

27:20.466 --> 27:22.628
Maybe your goal is I wanna read it every day, seven days a week.

27:23.049 --> 27:24.370
Okay, that's a big risk for you.

27:25.090 --> 27:27.253
We had a guy in our small group that wanted to do the exact same thing.

27:27.694 --> 27:30.278
So what we suggest is, okay, instead of doing it seven days a week, do it three.

27:30.738 --> 27:31.559
Better yet, do it two.

27:32.280 --> 27:34.384
And do it consistently, weekend and week out.

27:34.404 --> 27:38.490
And as you grow in confidence, you lessen that risk, you take more risk than you read it three days.

27:38.510 --> 27:39.371
Then you read four days.

27:39.892 --> 27:46.441
It's completely changed his life and the way he integrates scripture into his day to day activities, all by mitigating that risk.

27:46.461 --> 27:48.925
Last step, check in question.

27:48.945 --> 27:52.530
Check in question your plan as you receive new information.

27:52.930 --> 27:55.093
This is important because your plan might adapt.

27:55.173 --> 27:55.935
Things might adapt.

27:55.975 --> 27:56.716
Things might happen.

27:56.956 --> 27:59.901
And you might be in a different spot, so you've got to adapt and roll and move through it.

28:00.662 --> 28:02.424
Why is it so important to plan this way?

28:03.846 --> 28:04.728
Bill Gates would say this.

28:04.768 --> 28:14.162
He would say, most people overestimate what they can do in one year and underestimate what they can do in 10, which is why the failure rate for goals is so high right now.

28:14.754 --> 28:24.369
People get so excited about that beginning of year goal and they get so hyped up and they overestimate it, but they underestimate what they can do if they just had a little bit of planning and just had a little bit of consistency.

28:24.750 --> 28:26.953
And they just incorporated God into it along the way.

28:27.614 --> 28:29.036
Proverbs says this about your planning.

28:29.637 --> 28:32.882
Good planning and hard work lead to prosperity.

28:32.902 --> 28:34.144
So you wanna get to where you wanna go?

28:34.565 --> 28:37.329
It takes hard work but more importantly, it takes good planning.

28:37.830 --> 28:43.058
Hasty shortcuts taking the short way, taking that short route out of it, trying to buzz through it completely,

28:43.394 --> 28:44.896
That's going to lead you straight into poverty.

28:46.218 --> 28:49.182
We can't overlook this hard work aspect, which leads us to step three.

28:49.222 --> 28:51.165
This would be the execution step.

28:51.866 --> 28:53.027
This is one of my favorite steps.

28:53.488 --> 28:55.651
Another way of saying this is now it's time to do it.

28:57.934 --> 29:01.639
Amelia Earhart was the first woman to fly solo across the Atlantic Ocean.

29:01.659 --> 29:03.121
She is a bad woman.

29:03.141 --> 29:04.343
And this is a great quote from her.

29:04.523 --> 29:07.847
She said, the most effective way to do it is to do it.

29:09.490 --> 29:10.251
I love that.

29:10.311 --> 29:10.831
So good.

29:11.452 --> 29:12.754
She just makes it so simple.

29:13.506 --> 29:14.908
And here's the thing about execution.

29:14.968 --> 29:18.332
To execute something means to do something until it is finished.

29:18.813 --> 29:20.395
Nobody lives through an execution.

29:21.476 --> 29:22.618
You go until it is done.

29:23.659 --> 29:30.888
So to do this means you need to take the step, you need to get out of the planning phase, get out of the evaluation stage, and now it's time for you to do what you know you need to do.

29:31.809 --> 29:33.591
Don't get paralyzed by all the information.

29:33.671 --> 29:36.014
Don't get paralyzed by having the most efficient plan.

29:36.055 --> 29:37.236
Is this the best way I could do this?

29:37.296 --> 29:39.299
Is this the best way that don't worry about that?

29:39.799 --> 29:42.002
A good plan today is better than the perfect plan tomorrow.

29:42.338 --> 29:50.611
Take one step, take short, consistent steps, and you will get to where you want to go, whether it's with your walk with Christ, you walk with your finances, your kids, whatever it may be.

29:51.753 --> 29:53.556
Bruce Lee had this to say about consistency.

29:53.576 --> 29:56.981
He said long-term consistency, Trump's short-term intensity.

29:57.442 --> 30:07.858
You want your goals to last this year throughout the next 10 years, keep it consistent over the long-term, little steps day by day, and you will get to where you want to go and finish.

30:08.482 --> 30:09.423
Finish what you start.

30:09.583 --> 30:10.685
Like this is biblical.

30:10.705 --> 30:14.170
Ecclesiastes 7.8 says, finishing is better than starting.

30:15.191 --> 30:16.613
Finish what you set out to do.

30:16.653 --> 30:19.737
Don't just be a part of the 92% who are over the next year.

30:19.757 --> 30:20.799
So yeah, I started a lot of stuff.

30:20.819 --> 30:21.840
I had the best intentions.

30:23.662 --> 30:25.765
And here's the most important thing in Proverbs 16.3.

30:26.006 --> 30:28.008
I want you to read this.

30:28.068 --> 30:28.849
I want you to circle it.

30:28.869 --> 30:29.671
I want you to highlight it.

30:29.691 --> 30:31.113
Whatever you gotta do to remember this.

30:32.595 --> 30:38.162
Because ultimately, at the end of the next 10 years, if you evaluate as best as you can,

30:38.370 --> 30:46.820
If you get motivated, if you have a good plan, if you're disciplined through the tough times, and if you really work and you really execute, you're gonna see some change and good things might happen for you.

30:47.421 --> 30:49.203
